			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2018</a> paper:</span><br><i>Morbig: a static parser for POSIX shell</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/YannRégisGianas.html">Yann Régis-Gianas</a>, <a href="../profile/NicolasJeannerod.html">Nicolas Jeannerod</a>, <a href="../profile/RalfTreinen.html">Ralf Treinen</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3276604.3276615">10.1145/3276604.3276615</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2018s/paper02.html"><em>MORBIG: A Static Parser for POSIX Shell</em></a> (SLE 2018 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagM">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> The paper primarily contributes techniques for language definition (often syntax-related) as part of language design.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It includes substantial tool support or infrastructure relevant for engineering/using languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It relies on formal methods (definitions/proofs/semantic properties) beyond informal description.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5e.html"><span class="tagL">T5E: Empirical Evaluation</span></a><ul><li> It reports an empirical evaluation (experiments, study, benchmarks, or measurements).
</li></ul></li></ul>
